na</a><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;> Why is 100hp such a big deal????</td><td align=right valign="bottom"><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swnewtopic.GIF border=0 alt="New Topic"></a>  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddPollScreenFromWeb><img src=http://www.gaiahealing.com/everquest/swnewpoll.gif border=0 alt="New Poll"></a>  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a>  </td></tr><tr><td align=left><br>Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=2599.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=2599.topic&start=41&stop=44>3</a> </td><td align=right> <br> <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showPrevMessage?topicID=2599.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showNextMessage?topicID=2599.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#CCCCCC><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#8B0000 class=headings><font color=#000000>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#8B0000 class=headings><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bryath>Bryath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/02 2:36:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> Hey there, just a question I read the boards alot and see the higher end warriors all say HP HP HP HP HP.  Does 100hp really make a whit of difference with the higher end game?  I dont think 100hp would matter when I am tanking Vindi and he is nailing me for 150hp every two seconds.  Is the 100hp from an item more than that when worn?  Is it like Raw AC that depending on lvl will actually go up?  Example if at 57 I have the 6ac, 65hp ring on; when I hit 58 will that 65hp still be 65hp or does it increase with my level?  If not then loading up on 35hp earings over stats seems kinda silly to me.  Please help I am very confused. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=warlordcrystara>WarlordCrystara</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.attbi.com/~rnoble001/Emoticon/tombstone.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/02 2:42:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> It all adds up, more hp is more of a beating you can take, therefor making you able to tank a mob better. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=141022"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.houston.rr.com/apoctyliptic/pictures/boards/crystara/Crystara65.jpg " style="height:250;width:248;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
&quot;Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I shall fear no evil.<br>
For I am the meanist son of a bitch in the valley.&quot; <br>
- Marshall Crystara</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khuzdul69>Khuzdul69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/02 2:42:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> Rw + hps will only give you the hps shown.  100 HPS alone isn't much, but 40 hps here, 80 hps there, 100 hps somewhere else does build up and will eventually make the difference between someone with 3500 hps unbuffed at 60 and someone with 5000 hps unbuffed at 60.<br>
<br>
Also, even though 100 hps may only equal one more hit you can survive, that single hit that you survived can be the  fraction of a second or two seconds till his next combat round for for the CH to hit or Divine Interventionto proc causing the difference between surviving and not having to change tanks and dying causing a wipeout.  If you are not going to be tanking and not taking AoE damange, then who cares how much hps you have, go for some other stat if you like. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257207" *****"text-decoration: none">Khuzdul - Cleric</A><br>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257219" *****"text-decoration: none">Ologhai - Shadow Knight</A><br>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=454411" *****"text-decoration: none">Mandros - Warrior</A><br>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257272" *****"text-decoration: none">Vendetta - Rogue</A><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rani>rani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/02 3:15:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> Yes it does add up fast. So HP is still the main thing I look at when choosing gear. <br>
<br>
After HP it is probably resists I look at next. With PoP having alot of really nasty AEs, plus the changes that were recently made to resists, gear that have alot of +save vs all is also high on my wish list. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trulianthescaledmofo>Trulian the Scaled Mofo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/02 9:07:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.nl/nico.schelling/Manchild.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> I'd say its all the school of thought. Most people can remember the progression of what a warrior &quot;needs&quot; throughout the ages. Stats were big at one time, then AC, then it was a haste frenzy (still here), resists, and the HP craze. It's all good really, hit points make a tangible difference which is why many warriors prefer them over AC (which as Verant has stated makes effect above the &quot;soft cap&quot; of 1250). And truly, in the high end game, most items have oodles of both AC and HP. I wonder where it's going to go next really, it usually only takes one person to post a log of what they figure is working best for them and then people immediately jump over and begin to claim the &quot;new&quot; territory for their own. Pretty soon every warrior is a carbon copy. There is more than one way. <br>
<br>
<br>
Also aside from general warrior criticism, I'd like to point out that your gear's effectiveness depends largely on what you hunt. You may want to go for huge AC if you do 90% grouping 10% raiding, or HP if you're the main tank on raids most nights. Feel it out, don't let all these people tell you what is best (even if their opinion is valid, which most are).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Trulian Swiftblade - Ayonae Ro<br>
Nargnarg MuffinSpectre - Solusek Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/10/02 12:18:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> HP is the new craze because it's the easiest thing to notice.  It's very obvious to see what an extra 100 HP does for you.  Stuff like mitigation, avoidance, etc... you don't really see its effect without parsing.<br>
<br>
If we know for sure every 100 AC equals 10% reduction in damage taken, people will probably go into AC again (assuming a 9K warrior, getting 100 more AC would have the same effect as getting 1000 more HP, and it's probably easier to come up with 100 AC than 1K HP items).  But we do not.  The AC caps remains mostly a mystery to us.  Without knowing how the AC/avoidance/etc works, it's easiest to <br>
go for HP because the effect of HP is very obvious and easy to account for.  If you have 1K more HP it lets you tank that much longer and your CH chains can be that much slower before you still die.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90049">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dagroob>da Groob</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://enmity.net/Public/G.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/10/02 11:59:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> Phantron stated the way I feel. I can see 100hp, but I can't see the effect of 10ac, or a couple of saves. That, and when high end tanks have all stats maxed, and rediculous saves and AC, then that pretty much leaves only HP to increase that doesn't have a cap, visible or not. <p><HTML><center>
