</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaylonn>Gaylonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/10/02 12:59:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://bellsouthpwp.net/R/a/RafaelSmith/axe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> Since this is still my only character I still consider myself a newbie.  So I come here and read all the posts trying to get ideas on what I should upgrade and what stats to concentrate on.  First everything I saw said AC &gt; all until AC = 1200 or so.  Latley all i see is HP &gt; all.  Personally I do see the effect of AC upgrades or better yet my healers see the effect.  So I have decided to conentrate on AC until its capped then start working on HP.  What good is HP if the mobs are beating out of you fast?  I'll take 10 extra AC over 100hp anyday. Hell I'll take 10extra AC over anystat these days.<br>
<br>
Personally I wonder if it has more to do with the fact that the numerical value of HP is so much bigger and does not have a &quot;cap&quot; so we all get caught up trying to see how high we can get it.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=181233"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://bellsouthpwp.net/R/a/RafaelSmith/Gaylon_Sig5.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://bellsouthpwp.net/R/a/RafaelSmith/druid2.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:Century;font-size:medium;">Level 55 Warrior</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Sworn to serve and protect Druids everywhere</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www30.brinkster.com/djseng/SotO/default.asp">Scream of the Owl</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>      &quot;It's really very simple.  If you run...you DIE&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyrdlan>Wyrdlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/10/02 1:40:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-viatores.org/book.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> As I said before on another topic, it's because it's hard to see how big your dick is under all that armor.  A big AC number only lets your PREVENT damage, a big HP number lets you TAKE damage.  It's a problem of comparing the wrong numbers and not working the math out.<br>
<br>
It's like Shaman getting all bent out of shape about their HP numbers and having the wisdom of a drunk troll shadowknight.  You have to do the math, not just look at the pretty numbers.  If Canni IV is 1.8 to 1 mana, and Wisdom is 6 mana to 1 wis, then for that shaman you need to get 10 more HP for every point of wisdom you give up. In other words, if your wisdom (which is common for shaman) is 165 with KEI, you'd need almost a thousand more health to make up for the wisdom you don't have. <br>
<br>
If you don't LEARN the system, you won't ever BEAT the system.  Since no one can say 1 AC protects you by XXXX amount, it's hard to figure out exactly how much HP it's okay to give up.<br>
<br>
I'm convinced though, that if you get your Stamina and AC both as high as you can you'll probably be the happiest.  HP seems to come along for the ride once you get AC and STA up. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm38.showMessage?topicID=409.topic"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eq-viatores.org/sig.php"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=friedrick>Friedrick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/10/02 1:50:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> <br>
Part of the problem in my opinion has been VI making mobs with ridiculously high attack values.  It seems that no matter what the AC of the warrior, the mob still hits for full or near full very often.  When this is the case, your extra AC does very little if anything to help you.  The extra hit points however lets the healers have a little bit longer to land heals on you though.<br>
<br>
Another part of the problem is people assuming tanking exp mobs is the same as tanking boss mobs.  In an exp group a mob rarely does damage fast enough that a good healer cannot keep you alive.  Here the mobs don't usually hit for max and AC has meaning because it is comparable to the attack value of the mob.<br>
<br>
When tanking a boss mob though, a tank is usually spammed with heals or a CHeal chain is established.  The timing on that is normally worst case scenario based on a mobs max hit compared to the tanks hit points.  The random number generator can be a harsh mistress and one good string of hits will take down a tank if worst case isn't planned for.  AC is meaningless there but HP's extend the time between CHeals.<br>
<br>
