<br>
Let's take Aerin'Dar, quad 1400.  In 2 rounds you can *potentially* take 11200 damage.  That is beyond whatever buffer HP can provide for you.  If I have 5K HP but I take half as much damage as you with 9K on average due to my AC, then my HP will, on average, last longer than you.  Yes there will be the times where he just lands some high hits and I die, but there will be more times where you end up taking more damage due to lack of AC despite having 4K more HPs, as my 5K HP at half damage is equivalent of 10K at your AC.  People seem to be paranoid against the random number generator and wants to have enough HP to simply overpower the worst case scenario, but that's rather silly.  Back when people fought AoW, no one had enough HP to last 2 good rounds by AoW but people still beat him, and fairly reliably.  Sometimes it is just impossible to ensure that the mob has no way of killing you, but it doesn't mean you can't win. <br>
<br>
But since no one knows how much extra AC really gets you in turns of mitigating damage, this is all kind of irrelevant.  But don't assume AC doesn't matter.  When tanking mobs with AC debuff, you'll definitely feel the effect of having your AC go to much lower values than you're used to, and in those cases having more AC definitely helps a lot more than simply having more HPs. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90049">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=varaho1>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1173<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 5:24:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ~</span><hr size=1> People like hps because hp is 100% active at all times ( until you die that is ) <br>
