<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257272" *****"text-decoration: none">Vendetta - Rogue</A><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 8:41:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> These logs are old, certainly pre PoP and it seems like at least Innate Defense would further alter the AC cap.<br>
<br>
The argument against ATK of mobs is stupid.  The only case where AC wouldn't matter is if mobs's min and max hit are effectively same, or if it has infinte attack, or zero attack.  There are NO mobs in the game with such stats.  Just because it feels like a mob is hitting you for max 80% of the time doesn't say anything about AC matters or not.  You don't know if a mob would've hit you for max 100% or 81% of the time if you neglected your AC.  People are basically saying, 'well XXX smacks me pretty hard with Y AC, so it must be useless.&quot;  Wrong.  You don't know how much harder (or not) you'd have been smacked with different amounts of AC, and without this information, you don't know anything about the usefulness of AC.<br>
<br>
The truth of the HP &gt; all debate is that people are too lazy to parse so they just want to pile more HP because they know what that does for sure.  Whether a mob has high or low ATK makes no difference unless you know how this ATK responds to different values of AC, and obviously everyone who's saying it doesn't matter never parsed it.  I don't claim to have parsed it either and I do go for mostly HP items too, but it's just flat out igorance to not parse something and blindly believe that it doesn't work.  You know, when I get AC debuffed to 1100 or less I still can't see a very noticeable damage increase I take, even though this is well within the range where AC makes a significant difference.  Eyeballing is a very poor way to measure how effective AC is. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90049">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=boinshar>Boinshar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 9:20:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://frustrated.com/images/boinshar.gif height=102 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> Wydlan,<br>
<br>
Mana and HP are totally different, you will do well to remember that when you comment about shamans.<br>
<br>
Mana regen &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; max mana.<br>
<br>
Casters don't get a mana CH that'd bring our mana from 1 to full, keep that in mind.<br>
<br>
Having a 4000pt mana pool while regening at 20 per tick is horrible compared to having a 3000pt mana pool while regening at 55 per tick (any shaman with can4 and torpor can easily maintain that). With can5, this can reach ~75 per tick. This is just class based mana regen, no KEI, no bard, no BL, no FT, and no AAs.<br>
<br>
Mana usage is about attrition over time, not about max mana. For a class like the shaman, not getting beat down while slowing is far more important than having an extra 1000 max mana which is a reserve that almost never gets used. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=varaho1>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1174<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 12:51:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> OK then some people do not understand.<br>
<br>
Look at that sticky above, you know the one about Ubermob tanking.<br>
<br>
See all the numbers? All the values DB DI ?<br>
<br>
I will compress it as much as I can:<br>
<br>
Mobs attack you within a range of different hits. This means there is a set maximum and minimum amount of damage that you can be hit for when fighting a mob. You will be hit for maximum damage, you will be hit for minimum damage and you will be hit for numbers in between them.<br>
<br>
AC moves the distribution of hits to more of them being on the higher or lower end of this range. More AC will cluster the hits down to the minimum end and less ac allowing more hits up to the maximum end.<br>
<br>
It's not just a &quot;gut feeling&quot; people have it is a mathematical equation that is used. EQ is a computer game and like all other computer games it uses numbers and equations to run things, such as the combat engine.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong I hate the &quot;HP &gt; all&quot; mentality, but there is a reasoning behind it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shelrabbi>Shelrabbi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 323<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/02 1:01:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2599.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why is 100hp such a big deal????</span><hr size=1> I wanted to point out one thing Phantron was missing.<br>
<br>
While a mob may have the potential to hit you for 11,200 in any given round, and while your AC might protect you more at 1500 then at 1300, the mob still has a minimum you can be hit for. <br>
<br>
So I have 5K hps and 1700 AC. I NEVER get hit for full. But the mobs base damage is 700. I get quaded and flurried and I'm dead, end of story. With 9K hps and 1300 AC, I'm gonna get hit for full more often, but I'll be able to live longer.<br>
<br>
Remember that having a high AC isn't going to prevent you from taking damage, ever. It's going to make you take less, but only to a point. And if you don't have the hps to cover that bottom point, you're worthless as a tank. <p>Shelrabbi Hassida<BR>
